Terminology
State Variables
In a dynamical system (an Initial Value Problem)e dependent variables are also called state variables. e.g., in Problem 5HW #9, x v (or бәӢ) are the state variables. These variablrten put intoarrayis callee starray. While independent variable (usually time, us) is not technically consider state variable, we primarily interested ie system state atime. In our case, we will inserdependent variable ae first value in the state array callauged state array.

Mode Shaped Natural Frequencies
Consider vibra system below. As a two degreefreedom system, it has two natural frequencies two mode shapes. Ie two masses are both displaco the left (by thrrect distances) releasedey weach undergo perfect sinusoidal mo. Both will oscillate at same frequency вҖ“ called first natural frequencye first mode shape is a normalized vector representingpectsignmplitudes of their oscillations. second mode shapd second natural frequency occur whee two masses are releasfter being displaced (by thrrect distances)opposite directions. In  case, the values in the mode shapes wille different signs, because masses are movingopposite directions.

