Neglectfrine equations of mo system are:
бәҚ1 = (-(k1+k2)x1 + k2x2)/m1
бәҚ2 = (-(k2+k3)x2 + k2x1)/m2

where x1 x2 measured from the static equilibrium locations oe respec masses. To handle the 2nd order nature of the time derivas, we must include additional state variables v1 v2. If we arrange state variables ie order x1, v1, x2, v2e auged state array becomes t, x1, v1, x2, v2, and thrresponding differential equations becomes:
dx1/dt = g1(a) = a(3)
dv1/dt = g2(a) = (-(k1+k2)a(2) + k2a(4))/m1
dx2/dt = g3(a) = a(5)
dv2/dt = g4(a) = (-(k2+k3)a(4) + k2a(2))/m2

Remember, a(1)timedoes not appear in our equations of mo.
